title.narrative: Agricultural Growth Program –Agri-business and Value Chain Development project (AGP-AMDe)

description.narrative: (Ethiopia): The Agribusiness and Market Development (AMDe) activity directly supports the Government of Ethiopia's Agricultural Growth Program by employing a market-led approach; i.e., a "value chain" methodology, designed to identify and address constraints and market opportunities of six key value chains (wheat, maize, sesame, chickpea, coffee and honey) and stakeholders to stimulate market-led agro-enterprise and cooperative linkages with domestic, regional and international markets. AMD activities are intended to directly contribute to USAID's development objective of Increased Economic Growth with Resiliency in Rural Ethiopia through targeted intermediate results in the areas of (a) improved competitiveness of select value chains; (b) improved access to finance; (c) business enabling environment; and (d) innovation funds.
